1
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:28,991
OFFICIAL ENTRY
1969 FESTIVAL OF THE ARTS

2
00:00:30,163 --> 00:00:33,462
DAIEI STUDIOS

3
00:00:40,907 --> 00:00:47,210
FIRES ON THE PLAIN

4
00:00:52,685 --> 00:00:53,709
You idiot!

5
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,354
The hospital sends you back
and you obey?

6
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:59,855
There's no room here
for consumptives like you!

7
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,223
Go back!
Tell 'em you have nowhere to go.

8
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:05,091
They'll have to take you.

9
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:09,493
Why can't you
grasp the situation?

10
00:01:09,869 --> 00:01:13,498
We landed to the west
under enemy fire

11
00:01:13,706 --> 00:01:16,368
to reinforce units
at Tacloban.

12
00:01:16,576 --> 00:01:19,909
We lost two-thirds of our men.

13
00:01:20,780 --> 00:01:23,340
Our artillery was sunk in transit.

14
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:28,010
We tried to reach Burauen airfield

15
00:01:28,221 --> 00:01:30,246
by crossing
the central mountains,

16
00:01:30,457 --> 00:01:32,948
but without artillery,
it was impossible.

17
00:01:33,726 --> 00:01:35,990
The enemy's counterattack

18
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,494
forced all companies
to fan out across the valley.

19
00:01:39,365 --> 00:01:40,832
You know all that.

20
00:01:41,034 --> 00:01:44,003
We brought 12 days' rations
from Ormoc.

21
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:46,900
You really think there's any left?

22
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:51,237
Soldiers are taking turns
foraging for food.

23
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:56,542
You're coughing up blood
and can't even lift a sack of potatoes.

24
00:01:56,749 --> 00:01:58,410
In the thick of war,

25
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:01,246
your comrades gave you
five days' food to take to the hospital.

26
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:04,713
Three days later you returned,

27
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:07,950
saying they'd
pronounced you cured.

28
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:11,120
TB cured in three days?

29
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:14,858
With five days' food,
you should've stayed that long.

30
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:19,370
I sent you back to complain,
but the doctor claimed

31
00:02:19,572 --> 00:02:23,269
it wasn't five days' worth,
and it was all gone anyway?

32
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,205
What kind of imbecile are you?

33
00:02:26,079 --> 00:02:30,379
I don't begrudge you the food.

34
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:36,020
If you could work like the others,
then no problem.

35
00:02:36,956 --> 00:02:41,120
This company's shrunk
to the size of a platoon.

36
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:43,454
But we still have to eat!

37
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:46,288
The unit has split into three groups

38
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:49,593
taking turns foraging
for yams and bananas.

39
00:02:49,802 --> 00:02:54,364
They eat what they find
and bring some back for the others.

40
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:58,408
Then the next group goes.
Like goddamn beggars!

41
00:02:59,078 --> 00:03:01,103
This is the Imperial Army!

42
00:03:01,314 --> 00:03:03,805
It's a disgrace,
but what can I do?

43
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:06,315
We all have to pitch in.

44
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:10,387
You're nothing but a burden.
You should be ashamed!

45
00:03:11,324 --> 00:03:14,157
All I can do
as your squad leader

46
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:18,456
is send you back to the hospital
before everyone starts hating you.

47
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:23,494
If they don't admit you,
sit there until they do.

48
00:03:23,703 --> 00:03:26,638
If they still refuse,
then you must die!

49
00:03:28,107 --> 00:03:30,371
You weren't given
a hand grenade for nothing.

50
00:03:30,577 --> 00:03:33,478
If they send you away,
blow yourself up.

51
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:36,308
That will be your final duty.

52
00:03:39,652 --> 00:03:43,315
I, Private First Class Tamura,
will return to the hospital.

53
00:03:43,523 --> 00:03:46,253
If they do not admit me,
I will kill myself.

54
00:03:46,459 --> 00:03:49,121
Good!
Now buck up and go!

55
00:04:03,376 --> 00:04:05,936
Don't bother reporting
to the commander.

56
00:04:30,503 --> 00:04:33,666
I, PFC Tamura, will report
to the hospital as ordered.

57
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:40,843
Fall in!

58
00:04:41,347 --> 00:04:43,679
It's not easy for the squad leader.

59
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:47,319
He can only order the men
to dig air-raid shelters.

60
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:50,815
They don't even have shovels.

61
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,821
Just sticks
and old worn-out pans.

62
00:04:55,028 --> 00:04:58,589
I fill out
supply requisitions

63
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:00,891
with nowhere to send them.

64
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:05,230
The enemy doesn't even
bother with us anymore,

65
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:08,236
yet we still dig air-raid shelters.

66
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:11,501
You're better off at the hospital.

67
00:05:11,711 --> 00:05:14,976
The company CO can't help you.

68
00:05:15,181 --> 00:05:19,345
I'm sure he heard
the squad leader's hollering.

69
00:05:37,603 --> 00:05:39,628
Here are some rations.

70
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:43,966
I'm grateful.

71
00:05:57,657 --> 00:06:00,319
Kill yourself only if you have to.

72
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:39,263
Damn it, I'm starving.

73
00:07:18,838 --> 00:07:20,135
Hey!

74
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:25,401
Where are you going?

75
00:07:27,747 --> 00:07:30,875
I didn't think
anybody was around.

76
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:34,246
This is the entrance
to our camp.

77
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:38,686
Where there's an entrance,
there have to be sentries.

78
00:07:39,559 --> 00:07:42,084
It's so hot
we went in the shade.

79
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:44,058
Where are you going?

80
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:47,158
I, PFC Tamura,
am reporting to the hospital.

81
00:07:47,366 --> 00:07:49,391
The hospital again?

82
00:07:49,602 --> 00:07:51,866
I won't be returning
to the company.

83
00:07:52,371 --> 00:07:53,736
Why not?

84
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:58,508
It seems there's no room here
for sick men like me.

85
00:07:59,946 --> 00:08:01,914
Who said that?

86
00:08:02,114 --> 00:08:04,014
The CO?

87
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:06,447
The squad leader?

88
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:13,751
Who knows who's better off anyway,
you or us?

89
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:17,424
They'll order us to attack soon.

90
00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:20,465
But will the hospital take you?

91
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:24,536
I'll stick it out until they do.

92
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:26,837
Don't give up.

